dissonanceFlags.description: Filler words such as 'um' and 'ah' are used frequently.
dissonanceFlags.coaching: Reduce filler words to enhance clarity and professionalism.
dissonanceFlags.visualEvidence: Speaker pauses and looks away while using filler words

dissonanceFlags.description: Occasional glances down at notes break eye contact.
dissonanceFlags.coaching: Maintain consistent eye contact to build rapport with the audience.

dissonanceFlags.description: Adjusts hair and shifts weight slightly.
dissonanceFlags.coaching: Minimize fidgeting to appear more confident and professional.

dissonanceFlags.description: Gestures are used but could be more diverse.
dissonanceFlags.coaching: Use more varied gestures to keep the audience engaged.

dissonanceFlags.description: Pace quickens slightly during complex explanations.
dissonanceFlags.coaching: Ensure pacing matches the complexity of the content.
Maintain a consistent speaking pace to improve flow.

dissonanceFlags.coaching: Use gestures to emphasize points and engage the audience.

geminiReport.coachingAdvice:
The presentation demonstrated effective speaking pace and maintained composed body language throughout. Notably, the overall eye contact was strong, contributing to audience engagement.

However, there are clear opportunities for refinement. While eye contact was generally good, consistency in maintaining a direct gaze could be improved to sustain connection. The most significant area for development involves the frequent use of filler words, which can detract from message clarity and speaker credibility.
